{
  "texts": [
    "Korat tests based on a formal specification [8].",
    "Dart performs concolic test generation [18].",
    "Cute performs concolic testing for c [34].",
    "Our approach is conceptually related to coverage driven SBST approaches and Concolic Execution because it formulates test generation as a constraint solving problem for the LLM, where the LLM is guided to generate a test that will follow a specific execution path.",
    "However, instead of performing symbolic constraint solving to follow specific execution paths we give the LLM access to the focal method source code."
  ]
}